## 2. Chat Container & Real-time Messaging

### 2.1 Message Display Implementation
**File: `src/components/ChatContainer.jsx`**

**Key Concepts:**
- Real-time message rendering
- Auto-scroll functionality
- Socket.io subscription management
- Message bubble positioning

**Code Analysis:**
```jsx
// File: src/components/ChatContainer.jsx
const ChatContainer = () => {
  const { messages, getMessages, selectedUser, subscribeToMessages, unsubscribeFromMessages } = useChatStore();
  const { authUser } = useAuthStore();
  const messageEndRef = useRef(null);

  // Fetch messages and subscribe to real-time updates
  useEffect(() => {
    getMessages(selectedUser._id);
    subscribeToMessages();
    return () => unsubscribeFromMessages();
  }, [selectedUser._id]);

  // Auto-scroll to newest messages
  useEffect(() => {
    if (messageEndRef.current && messages) {
      messageEndRef.current.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth" });
    }
  }, [messages]);

  return (
    <div className="flex-1 flex flex-col overflow-auto">
      <ChatHeader />
      <div className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-4 space-y-4">
        {messages.map((message) => (
          <div
            key={message._id}
            className={`chat ${message.senderId === authUser._id ? "chat-end" : "chat-start"}`}
            ref={messageEndRef}
          >
            <div className="chat-image avatar">
              <img src={message.senderId === authUser._id ? authUser.profilePic : selectedUser.profilePic} />
            </div>
            <div className="chat-header">
              <time>{formatMessageTime(message.createdAt)}</time>
            </div>
            <div className="chat-bubble flex flex-col">
              {message.image && <img src={message.image} className="sm:max-w-[200px] rounded-md mb-2" />}
              {message.text && <p>{message.text}</p>}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <MessageInput />
    </div>
  );
};
```

**Learning Points:**
- **useRef Hook**: `messageEndRef` for DOM element reference and auto-scrolling
- **Effect Cleanup**: Returning cleanup function for socket unsubscription
- **Conditional CSS**: Dynamic chat bubble positioning based on sender
- **Array Mapping**: Rendering messages with unique keys

