## 4. Chat Header & Sidebar Components

### 4.1 Chat Header with Online Status
**File: `src/components/ChatHeader.jsx`**

```jsx
// File: src/components/ChatHeader.jsx
const ChatHeader = () => {
  const { selectedUser, setSelectedUser } = useChatStore();
  const { onlineUsers } = useAuthStore();

  return (
    <div className="p-2.5 border-b border-base-300">
      <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
        <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
          <img src={selectedUser.profilePic || "/avatar.png"} />
          <div>
            <h3>{selectedUser.fullName}</h3>
            <p>{onlineUsers.includes(selectedUser._id) ? "Online" : "Offline"}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <button onClick={() => setSelectedUser(null)}>
          <X />
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};
```

### 4.2 Sidebar with User Filtering
**File: `src/components/Sidebar.jsx`**

```jsx
// File: src/components/Sidebar.jsx
const Sidebar = () => {
  const { users, selectedUser, setSelectedUser } = useChatStore();
  const { onlineUsers } = useAuthStore();
  const [showOnlineOnly, setShowOnlineOnly] = useState(false);

  const filteredUsers = showOnlineOnly
    ? users.filter((user) => onlineUsers.includes(user._id))
    : users;

  return (
    <aside className="h-full w-20 lg:w-72 border-r">
      <div className="p-5">
        <label>
          <input
            type="checkbox"
            checked={showOnlineOnly}
            onChange={(e) => setShowOnlineOnly(e.target.checked)}
          />
          Show online only
        </label>
      </div>
      
      <div className="overflow-y-auto">
        {filteredUsers.map((user) => (
          <button
            key={user._id}
            onClick={() => setSelectedUser(user)}
            className={selectedUser?._id === user._id ? "bg-base-300" : ""}
          >
            <img src={user.profilePic || "/avatar.png"} />
            {onlineUsers.includes(user._id) && <span className="bg-green-500 rounded-full" />}
            <div>{user.fullName}</div>
          </button>
        ))}
      </div>
    </aside>
  );
};
```

**Learning Points:**
- **Array Filtering**: `users.filter()` for online user filtering
- **Responsive Design**: `hidden lg:block` classes
- **Status Indicators**: Visual online/offline indicators

